    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-08-17T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-08-17T04:00:00-05:00" n="729"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d729">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/135: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-17T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 17, 1931—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 17—8:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>106. Your 91, August 15, noon.<note n="50" xml:id="d729fn50">Not printed.</note>
                    It is definitely anticipated by League Secretariat that the report of the
                    experts who meet today in Geneva cannot be transmitted to the two distant
                    Governments interested, <pb facs="0812" n="692" xml:id="pg_692"/> namely, the
                    United States and Liberia, in time to permit the Committee to meet and submit
                    recommendations to the forthcoming session of the Council. It is impossible now
                    to give even an approximate date when the Committee might be convened but the
                    Secretariat sees no probability of such a meeting before the close of the
                    Assembly in September.</p>
                <p>The report will be sent to all members of the Committee and Liberia. The United
                    States and Liberia were mentioned specifically in my 105, August 14, midnight
                        [<hi rend="italic">noon</hi>],<note n="50a" xml:id="d729fn50a">Not
                        printed.</note> to emphasize the time element.</p>
                <p>Such additional information as may be obtained during or directly following the
                    experts’ session will be telegraphed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
